        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer35926557" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16013298675613913066">This is not the best James book. It&apos;s not a bad book, but it&apos;s not the best. There is one plot development that does seem to come a bit out of left field. <br/><br/>Outside of that, this is still good James. She takes time with her characters, and this is really her strength as a writer. She shows people as human, and not a classic bad guy and good guy way. Even if we don&apos;t like a character, James still makes the reader feel something for the character, perhaps pity. This makes the people in the books hum</span>
  <span id="freeText16013298675613913066" style="display:none">This is not the best James book. It's not a bad book, but it's not the best. There is one plot development that does seem to come a bit out of left field. <br /><br />Outside of that, this is still good James. She takes time with her characters, and this is really her strength as a writer. She shows people as human, and not a classic bad guy and good guy way. Even if we don't like a character, James still makes the reader feel something for the character, perhaps pity. This makes the people in the books human.</span>
