<div id="review_2028890061" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2028890061" />
    <a title="Tracie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2004747-tracie"><img alt="Tracie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1515778265p2/2004747.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2028890061?book_show_action=true">Jun 14, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tracie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tracie" href="/user/show/2004747-tracie">Tracie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2004747-tracie?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2028890061" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8562417807669975464">PD James and I seem to have a pattern. I start off, engaged and interested. Then, as the grisly details unfold, I (again) notice that there frequently is a deviant sexual undertone/fetish associated with the crimes, and I sigh heavily, roll my eyes, and think to myself, &quot;this will be the last one I read. This is getting old&quot;. But, I keep reading, as I&apos;m making my deductions, etc. (She usually fools me--but not all the time!) Yup, she&apos;s done her job.<br/><br/>Then, as she reveals the Who/What/When/Where/Wh</span>
  <span id="freeText8562417807669975464" style="display:none">PD James and I seem to have a pattern. I start off, engaged and interested. Then, as the grisly details unfold, I (again) notice that there frequently is a deviant sexual undertone/fetish associated with the crimes, and I sigh heavily, roll my eyes, and think to myself, "this will be the last one I read. This is getting old". But, I keep reading, as I'm making my deductions, etc. (She usually fools me--but not all the time!) Yup, she's done her job.<br /><br />Then, as she reveals the Who/What/When/Where/Why, the captivation returns. Then, she ends with a gorgeous, self-reflective, elegantly final closing paragraph or two...and I soften.<br /><br />Will I read yet another? Hmm...<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="8562417807669975464" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


