        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3092859567" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12599796798807495879">This was not my favorite P D James mystery, but to be fair, I typically love them so it is a high bar. It met my expectations in that I was 93% complete before I was certain who killed the victim. I guessed this person at about 50% through, but followed some delightful &quot;goose-chases&quot; after that point. My main problem with this one is that Adam is not the main detective. He is on holiday in the area and has to watch a former colleague do most of the leg-work. I have come to love being in Adam&apos;s m</span>
  <span id="freeText12599796798807495879" style="display:none">This was not my favorite P D James mystery, but to be fair, I typically love them so it is a high bar. It met my expectations in that I was 93% complete before I was certain who killed the victim. I guessed this person at about 50% through, but followed some delightful "goose-chases" after that point. My main problem with this one is that Adam is not the main detective. He is on holiday in the area and has to watch a former colleague do most of the leg-work. I have come to love being in Adam's mind while he investigates a crime and I didn't get as much of that in this one. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12599796798807495879" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


